      "span_text": "The basic notions about Alfven wave interaction with a turbulent layer (TL) with anomalous fieldCopyright c The Society of Geomagnetism and Earth, Planetary and Space Sciences (SGEPSS); The Seismological Society of Japan; The Volcanological Society of Japan; The Geodetic Society of Japan; The Japanese Society for Planetary Sciences; TERRAPUB. aligned resistance were formulated by [CITATION_1] , who showed that waves can partially penetrate a layer, be absorbed in it, and reflect from it.",
